article.headline: Pennsylvania 70, Dartmouth 51
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Ibrahim Jaaber made nine of eleven field goal attempts and scored a game-high 21 points to lead the University of Pennsylvania to a 70-51 victory over Dartmouth Friday. Jaaber added five steals and five rebounds as Pennsylvania improved to 13-6 overall and 5-0 in conference play. David Whitehurst chipped in 14 points and Eric Osmundson had 13 points for the Quakers, who beat Dartmouth for the 18th-consecutive time. Mike Lang led the Big Green with 14 points while Paul Bode had a game-high 14 rebounds off the bench. Dartmouth is now 3-17 overall and 1-6 in the Ivy League. Leading by 11 points midway through the second half, Penn used a 12-4 run to build a 63-44 lead, its biggest to that point. The Quakers shot 55.6 percent from the field to win handily on a night when they turned the ball over 19 times. Dartmouth was limited to 39.4 percent shooting and turned the ball over 18 times.
